    "Therefore, we used one language model (ESM-1v) and one inverse folding model (ProteinMPNN) in COMPSS.",
    "Our study does not benchmark generative models against each other but instead evaluates metrics to identify those widely applicable across models and enzyme families.",
    "Nevertheless, we found that ASR outperforms neural network models in naive generation, indicating room for improvement in protein deep generative models.",
    "We observed a wide range of AUC-ROC scores for different combinations of the generative model, enzyme family and metric.",
    "Different models and enzyme families may have different failure modes captured by different metrics."
